			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-740064">
									

<p>I liked it a lot. I also liked the writing beyond the first paragraph, whose sentences seemed a bit long and stilted.</p>
<p>I always enjoy a story which fleshes out a character of the Foundation mythos. Is this suppose to fit into a series of stories about Senior Staff introducing their protégés as the new guard? Like Clef's recent story set in the future, the end of Wanderlust, and A Evening with Bright.</p>

